lu_part1: Wie laang schléift, schléift sech waarm;
lu_part2: wie fréi opsteet, ësst sech aarm.
en_literal_translation_p1: He who grinds long, grinds himself warm;
en_literal_translation_p2: he who gets up early, eats himself poor.
en_closest_real_corresponding_saying_p1: The early bird catches the worm,
en_closest_real_corresponding_saying_p2: but the second mouse gets the cheese.
